Gigabit











THE SKY IS THE LIMIT 
We’re building Gigabit Fiber Internet in cities with the most Sonic customers. Help bring our symmetric Gigabit to your city by signing up for Sonic and spreading the word, bringing you one step closer to that wind-in-your-hair, Gigabit speed you’ve always wanted.























Fiber is currently available in these cities:



San Francisco




Brentwood




Sebastopol








What is Gigabit Fiber Internet?


How fast is Gigabit Fiber?
Sonic's Gigabit Fiber Internet is a fiber-to-the-premise internet connection. Our fiber cables transfer data 1000 Megabits per Second, up to 50x faster than the average download speed in America. And with our symmetric Gigabit Fiber service, that speed goes both ways, meaning that the lightning-fast speed of your uploads now matches your downloads.
What does that mean for me?
That means you can count on the fastest internet speed in the U.S., and you get our award-winning support team and highest-ranked privacy practices at your fingertips. 







