Mediacom Communications Corporation Headquarters in Blooming Grove, NY


Mediacom is a cable television and communications provider in the United States. Founded in 1995 by Rocco B. Commisso,[1] it serves primarily smaller markets in the Midwest and Southern United States. Formerly a publicly traded firm, it went private in a $600 million transaction in March 2011 and is, as of 2011, owned by Commisso.[2]



